article.headline: Northwestern St. 69, Stephen F. Austin 63
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Tyronn Mitchell scored 15 points and Jermaine Wallace added 14 to lead Northwestern State to a 69-63 victory over Stephen F. Austin on Thursday night. Mitchell hit 4-of-6 from the field, including 3-4 from 3-point range. Wallace hit 7-of-12 from the field. Stephen F. Austin (6-6, 0-1 Southland) led 34-23 at the half after shooting 58 percent from the field. Northwestern State (7-8, 1-0) took the lead for good at 9:43 left in the second half. The Demons shot 60 percent from the field in the second half. Anthony Paez led Stephen F. Austin with 19 points and Hank Rivers added 11. Jermaine Spencer added 12 points for Northwestern State.
